--- Which face indices are non-allowed? ---
    face_1: non-allowed 96 times
    face_2: non-allowed 96 times

--- face_0 analysis ---
  face_0 (remove v_0) is allowed: 192 paths
  face_0 is NOT allowed: 0 paths
  face_0 injective on ALL Ham paths: 64/64
  face_{n-1} injective on ALL Ham paths: 64/64

  ** TRIVIAL FACT: face_0 is ALWAYS injective on Hamiltonian paths **
  Reason: A Ham path uses ALL n vertices. Removing v_0 gives (v_1,...,v_3).
  This determines which vertex was v_0 (the missing one). So face_0 is injective.
  Similarly, face_i is injective on Ham paths for ANY fixed i.

